Convert protoc-gen-c/compat.h's angle-bracket absl include to a quoted one
so Bazel's default -iquote external/abseil-cpp+/ lookup satisfies it.  Angle
brackets would require -I/-isystem, which abseil's cc_library doesn't
contribute (it has no `includes` attr), and threading a per-version repo
canonical path through copts is brittle.  Quoted is equivalent semantically
for this header (the file is unambiguously the upstream absl one).

--- a/protoc-gen-c/compat.h
+++ b/protoc-gen-c/compat.h
@@ -36,7 +36,7 @@
 #endif

 #if GOOGLE_PROTOBUF_VERSION >= 6030000
-# include <absl/strings/string_view.h>
+# include "absl/strings/string_view.h"
 #else
 # include <string>
 #endif
